      • getExecutionId

        public long getExecutionId()
        By default a new unique executionId is assigned to each new ExecutionEnvironment (assignNewExecutionId). Can be set manually to create a batch of ExecutionEnvironment that are semantically a "single launch". RunContentDescriptors will not reuse each other tabs if they have the same executionId.
        Returns:
        An id that will be propagated to resulting RunContentDescriptor.
